  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nVersion: 1.10.20-unstable\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nGo Version: go1.18.3\r\nOperating System: linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI am simply trying to query a deployed contract - in particular the ```balanceOf()``` function\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm getting an \"insufficient funds for transfer\" error. Geth thinks I am trying to perform a write function, when clearly the ```balanceOf()``` function is just a read (as the abi also says - \" stateMutability \":  \"view \") \r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```var abi = [<the abi implementation from etherscan>]```\r\n\r\n```var contract = web3.eth.contract(abi);```\r\n\r\n```var contract_instance = contract.at(<contract address (proxy)>);```\r\n\r\n```contract_instance.balanceOf(<some wallet with a balance>);```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nError: insufficient funds for transfer\r\n\tat web3.js:6365:9(45)\r\n\tat send (web3.js:5099:62(34))\r\n\tat web3.js:4155:41(50)\r\n\tat apply (native)\r\n\tat web3.js:4241:75(21)\r\n\tat bound  (native)\r\n\tat <eval>:1:1(3)\r\n````\r\n",
